news.title: NGT directs Nimawat Granite to pay interim compensation for violating green norms
news.para: ​A bench of chairperson Justice A K Goel noted that the company had filed an application stating it had complied with the environmental norms but the annexed documents did not conclusively show it actually did.

news.title: Goa: Co-working space on four beaches approved, one within turtle centre
news.para: At Miramar, the co-working space will be created near the Manohar Parrikar Samadhi complex, while in the case of Morjim there will be a co-working space cum turtle nesting interpretation centre, as this stretch of the coast in Pernem sees nesting by Olive Ridley turtles.

news.title: SBI hikes MCLR by up to 15 bps across tenors
news.para: The benchmark one-year MCLR, which is used as base for fixing most of home, auto and personal loans, has been raised by 10 basis points (bps) to 8.05 per cent, as against 7.95 per cent earlier.

news.title: FHRAI writes to Sebi to stop OYO from launching IPO after CCI penalty
news.para: In October this year, the Competition Commission of India (CCI) slapped penalties totalling more than Rs 392 crore on online travel firms MakeMyTrip, Goibibo, and hospitality services provider OYO for indulging in unfair business practices.

news.title: Keystone Realtors IPO subscribed 41% on Day 2 of offer
news.para: The category for non-institutional investors was subscribed 72 per cent, Qualified Institutional Buyers (QIBs) portion received 49 per cent subscription and Retail Individual Investors (RIIs) 24 per cent.

news.title: Cash-strapped Bengaluru civic body yet to recover Rs 1,000 crore from builders
news.para: The BBMP collects ground rent, licence fee, building licence fee, scrutiny fee and miscellaneous fee for sanctioning plans from builders.

news.title: New Zealand house prices see biggest fall since the 1990s
news.para: The house price index, which measures changes in house prices on a like for like basis, fell for the 11th consecutive month and is now down 10.9% on October last year, according to data released by the Real Estate Institute of New Zealand on Tuesday.

news.title: Land Securities to hold back re-investments in challenging economic climate
news.para: Landsec, Britain's top commercial property landlord, said its pace of re-investment would slow down over the next year or so because of the challenging economic climate.

news.title: Emaar Properties' net profit rises 46% to $408.40 million in Q3 2022
news.para: Emaar said its first nine months of 2022 were "underpinned by robust property sales and growth in the performance of recurring revenue businesses".

news.title: Sunac China seeks to restructure its $2.1 billion in onshore bonds: Sources
news.para: The Beijing-based developer has extended repayment for a 4 billion yuan bond due earlier this year, and is restructuring its offshore debt after missing some payments.

news.title: Assam government rolls out scheme to provide land rights to natives
news.para: Sarma said the cabinet has also advised that people in char areas will not get this benefit. “We have to see from the ecological point to save our rivers. Majuli island is an exception since it is of permanent nature,” he added.

news.title: Nagpur: Sudama Talkies to make way for multi-storey commercial complex
news.para: “The old name Sudama would be retained,” said Praneet Singh, the third generation owner of the theatre. The new property would be constructed by R Sandesh Group and Murarka Group, which have now entered the scene.

news.title: Nashik: Property tax department to intensify recovery drive
news.para: Nashik municipal commissioner Chandrakant Pulkundwar has set a deadline of December-end for the property tax department to complete the property tax collection target of Rs 150 crore set for the current financial year.

news.title: Property investment in China falls 16% year-on-year in October 2022
news.para: Property investment fell 16.0% year-on-year in October -- its biggest drop since January-February 2020, according to Reuters calculations based on data from the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS). It slumped 12.1% in September.

news.title: SC to hear Chintels Paradiso residents' plea on November 21
news.para: The residents have also challenged the report of a special investigation team (SIT) constituted by the administration to probe the February incident.
